  <steps>
    <step num="0">In a heavy bottom pot, combine the olive oil, onion, celery, and carrots over medium heat. Cook until the carrots soften and the onions become slightly translucent. </step>
    <step num="1">Add the garlic and salt, and cook for an additional 2 minutes. </step>
    <step num="2">Add the green beans, sauce, and water, and bring to a boil. </step>
    <step num="3">Add the beans and macaroni and cook for about 9-10 minutes until the macaroni is al dente. </step>
    <step num="4">Serve warm with Parmesan and basil. </step>
    <step num="5">Enjoy! </step>
